Review text: Often heard about this place, and finally decided to give it a try. I am a coffee drinker however mostly never wanted to try a new place due to some people just couldn't listen to my preference. Surprisingly in here they took my order seriously and the coffee came really nice. This is a first for me. The pastry is also nice although I would still prefer the coffee. Definitely a place to hangout with friends and families. The coffee was good, their butter croissant was worth to try. Prices was also reasonable.
It's better to go in the morning or when the sun is already not too harsh.
a must visit if you enjoy drinking coffee, try the cold brew sampler, will definitely blew your mind!
nice place, pastry dan minumannya enak. bit pricey for me, but overall great.

I thought Melbourne was the coffee capital, but then I came to Bali and coffee has never been the same again.
If you love coffee and want to drink the best coffee in the world and learn about coffee, go to Seniman.
Here you can taste all the different coffees, experience the flavour profiles, and learn all about production and brewing methods.
The breakfast is great and if you like smashed avocado on sourdough and you thought only Melbourne could do it right; this place puts Melbourne to shame. Breakfast is delicious here.
The atmosphere is trendy and clever. For example: they have converted flimsy plastic deck chairs into solid comfortable rocking chairs with a very simple modification.
The staff are delightful and friendly, service is quick and always comes with a smile. No trip to Ubud would be complete without visiting this place.

Best flat white I had in Bali, if not one of the best I‚Äôve had. Has a nice nutty and chocolatey tasting notes. The price of their beans are very reasonable too. The pastries at the counter looked really yummy pity was too full to try
Nice spot at ubud

Probably the best black coffee I‚Äôve had, in Bali, or anywhere.

nice place for chill and quality time with your family or friend. They serve artisan coffee, tea, and chocolate. I love the presentation of the beverages. I ordered ginger tea latte, nice to drink when its raining. I apreciated staff here was so humble and friendly,

Yummy food and friendly staff... Lved the waffles... And a great English breakfast...

Review text: Located in a small lane near the city center, this coffee shop is quite difficult to search. I came here because of my friends recommendation. And voila! Their coffee is very good... I would happily came here again when i visit Ubud, and would recommend it to any of my friends...
